  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "In a bowl, mix flour and sugar. Add butter and salt until crumbly mixture forms.",
    "Gently toss sweet potatoes with half the crumble mixture in a pan until coated evenly.",
    "Place sweet potatoes on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, then top with remaining crumble mixture.",
    "Top with halved peppadew peppers cut-side down. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "Serve warm as dessert."
